Breakables is a term primarily used by [[drummers]] to refer to a set of customized hardware that is part of their drum kit. Breakables typically consist of;

1) Cymbals, including high-hats
2) Snare drum
3) Kick pedal
4) Drummer's stool

Typically, the cymbal stands are considered to be part of the base kit and are usually not considered breakables.

Breakables are separated from the base kit, for a number of reasons. Primarily because the breakables are the most customizable pieces of the kit, every drummer will have a different tone and sound quality from their breakables that they'll want to achieve. The second reason is that they are the most sensitive pieces of a drum kit and are the most likely to become damaged (especially the snare drum, which is typically hit at least once or twice per bar in rock, blues, country or soul music).